  "text": "Django's CSRF protection is implemented across multiple coordinated components:\n\n## Core CSRF Middleware (django/middleware/csrf.py)\nThe CsrfViewMiddleware class is the foundation of Django's CSRF protection. Key implementation details:\n\n1. **Token Validation Chain**: The process_view method initiates validation, calling _check_token which:\n   - Retrieves the CSRF secret from cookies or sessions via _get_secret\n   - Extracts the request token from POST data or HTTP headers\n   - Validates token format using _check_token_format\n   - Compares tokens using _does_token_match, which calls constant_time_compare for timing-attack-safe comparison\n\n2. **Token Masking (BREACH Protection)**: \n   - _mask_cipher_secret: Creates a masked token by combining a random mask with the secret using XOR-like operations\n   - _unmask_cipher_token: Recovers the original secret from a masked token\n   - Tokens are masked when sent to clients but unmasked for comparison\n\n3. **Origin and Referer Validation**:\n   - _origin_verified: Validates Origin headers against CSRF_TRUSTED_ORIGINS\n   - _check_referer: Strict referer checking for HTTPS requests\n   - Both methods prevent cross-domain attacks\n\n4. **Timing-Attack Prevention**:\n   - _does_token_match (line 143-157) uses constant_time_compare from django.utils.crypto\n   - This prevents attackers from using timing differences to guess valid tokens\n\n## CSRF Decorators (django/views/decorators/csrf.py)\nProvides view-level CSRF protection without middleware:\n- csrf_protect: Wraps CsrfViewMiddleware for individual views\n- csrf_exempt: Marks views exempt from CSRF checks\n- requires_csrf_token: Ensures token availability without enforcement\n- ensure_csrf_cookie: Guarantees CSRF cookie is set in response\n\n## Timing-Attack-Safe Comparison (django/utils/crypto.py)\nThe constant_time_compare function (line 65-67) uses secrets.compare_digest to prevent timing attacks. This is critical because:\n- Compares tokens in constant time regardless of where they differ\n- Prevents attackers from determining token validity through timing analysis\n- Used exclusively in _does_token_match for token validation\n\n## Template Integration\n1. **CsrfTokenNode (django/template/defaulttags.py)**:\n   - Implements {% csrf_token %} template tag\n   - Renders hidden input field with masked token\n   - Retrieves token from template context (csrf_token variable)\n\n2. **Context Processors (django/template/context_processors.py)**:\n   - csrf function provides csrf_token to RequestContext\n   - Lazily evaluates get_token to avoid unnecessary computation\n\n3. **Lazy Utilities (django/template/backends/utils.py)**:\n   - csrf_token_lazy: Lazily evaluates get_token\n   - csrf_input_lazy: Lazily renders complete hidden input field\n   - Supports both Django templates and Jinja2\n\n## CSRF Failure Handling (django/views/csrf.py)\nThe csrf_failure view handles rejected requests:\n- Displays informative error page when CSRF validation fails\n- Configurable via CSRF_FAILURE_VIEW setting\n- Provides debugging information in DEBUG mode\n- Includes specific messages for different failure reasons (missing cookie, missing referer, etc.)\n\n## Security Checks (django/core/checks/security/csrf.py)\nPerforms configuration validation:\n- check_csrf_middleware: Warns if CsrfViewMiddleware not enabled\n- check_csrf_cookie_secure: Warns if CSRF_COOKIE_SECURE not set to True\n- check_csrf_failure_view: Validates CSRF failure view signature and importability\n\n## Complete Validation Chain\nRequest → CsrfViewMiddleware.process_view() → _check_token() → _get_secret() → _check_token_format() → _does_token_match() → constant_time_compare() → Accept/Reject → csrf_failure() (on rejection)\n\nAlternatively, with decorators:\nRequest → csrf_protect decorator → CsrfViewMiddleware logic (same as above)\n\nToken rendering flow:\nTemplate → {% csrf_token %} → CsrfTokenNode.render() → csrf context processor → get_token() → _mask_cipher_secret() → HTML output"
